   FABRI-CENTERS OF AMERICA Inc. (Cleveland) -- James Monro
Jr., executive vice president, was named to the new post of
chief operating officer of this chain of 621 fabric stores.
Mr. Monro, 40 years old, will be responsible for store
operations, in addition to his existing duties for
merchandising, advertising and merchandise allocation. Robert
Norton, 43, executive vice president and chief financial
officer, was named to the new post of chief administrative
officer. Mr. Norton's responsibilities now include physical
distribution and human resources along with his existing
responsibilities of management information systems,
accounting, internal audit and financial services, the
company said.
